                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donor (and his relatives) and the scribe.&#xD;
Four lines (in both columns) in the incipit page of Text I (fol. 3r), divided into two groups alternating with black lines;&#xD;
the first two lines in the incipit of Text II (fol. 20va); &#xD;
the first three lines of incipit of Text III (fol. 22ra); &#xD;
